 concomitantly, a vast audience for fiction in the 1840s and 1850s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAmerican fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aBook reviewingxHistoryy19th century. 0aBooks and readingzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aCriticismzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aU.S. History. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501726187?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501726187zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501726187/original  a978-3-11-053617-1 Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA